          <h2>üîç Experiment Title:</h2>
          <h3>To Find the Unknown Weight of a Body using Rectangular Components of Forces</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="experiment-section">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i> üéØ Learning Objectives:</h4>
          <ul class="objectives-list">
            <li>Understand the concept of force resolution into rectangular components.</li>
            <li>Learn to apply vector addition of forces in equilibrium.</li>
            <li>Experimentally determine an unknown weight using force balancing.</li>
            <li>Use a Gravesand's apparatus to visualize the equilibrium of concurrent forces.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="experiment-section">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> üõ†Ô∏è How to Perform the Experiment:</h4>
          <div class="procedure-steps">
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>1. Setup:</h5>
              <p>Place the Gravesand's apparatus on a smooth, horizontal surface vertically upright.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>2. Prepare Threads and Load:</h5>
              <p>Tie three threads at one end. Attach hangers with known weights on two ends and a bob of unknown weight on the third.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>3. Mount Threads:</h5>
              <p>Pass the threads over frictionless pulleys, adjusting weights so the central knot stays near the paper center.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>4. Mark Lines:</h5>
              <p>Place a plane mirror under each thread and mark their positions on a white paper sheet.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>5. Draw Force Lines:</h5>
              <p>Remove the sheet and draw lines from the knot point representing each thread's direction.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>6. Measurement:</h5>
              <p>Measure weights of hangers and bob using a spring balance.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="procedure-step">
              <h5>7. Graphical Force Resolution:</h5>
              <p>Use a chosen scale to represent forces as vectors and resolve known forces into components.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="experiment-section">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> ‚úÖ What You Will Learn:</h4>
          <ul class="outcomes-list">
